The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a statement on the one-year anniversary of the Westgate Mall attack in Nairobi, Kenya. The attack, carried out by al-Shabaab, resulted in the death of 67 people and injured around 200 others. The statement expresses condolences to the families and loved ones affected by the attack and emphasizes the United States' commitment to supporting Kenya in their fight against al-Shabaab and other terrorist groups. It also highlights the determination to not let these acts of terror weaken resolve.